    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="45"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d45fn1">Apparently sent via military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-16">October 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 459. Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <list>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>I entirely agree with the telegram you have sent to Uncle <gloss
                            target="#t_Joe1">Joe</gloss> about <gloss target="#t_Eureka1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eureka</hi>
                        </gloss>. Let me know what he replies.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Please also see Saint Mark 9 verses 5 and 6 especially sixth verse.<note
                            n="2" xml:id="d45fn2">
                            <p>The following footnote was typed on the source text by the White
                                House Map Room:</p>
                            <p>“Saint Mark 9</p>
                            <list>
                                <item>“5. And <persName corresp="#p_PII1">Peter</persName> answered
                                    and said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: and let
                                    us make three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and
                                    one for Elias.</item>
                                <item>“6. For he wist not what to say; for they were sore
                                    afraid.”</item>
                            </list>
                        </note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
